34:30.736 --> 34:35.072
♪ I want it all or not at all ♪

34:35.074 --> 34:39.209
♪ I can see reckoning,
reckoning ♪

34:44.650 --> 34:47.651
♪ I'd rather watch
my kingdom fall ♪

34:51.123 --> 34:54.091
♪ I want it all or not at all. ♪

35:00.165 --> 35:02.132
You say some of my lands
are now a part of Scotland.

35:02.134 --> 35:05.135
How many lands?

35:05.137 --> 35:07.304
Half a dozen more
than we thought possible.

35:07.306 --> 35:08.605
They were disputable regions.

35:08.607 --> 35:09.773
But they were English!

35:09.775 --> 35:13.677
Until she married Darnley.

35:13.679 --> 35:15.112
Get out!

35:17.616 --> 35:19.649
Take your leave,
Lord Blackburn.

35:19.651 --> 35:21.218
No.

35:23.689 --> 35:26.790
Damn your ego!

35:26.792 --> 35:29.659
Insisting on having a son
when you had me!

35:29.661 --> 35:33.196
(crying):
Your own flesh and blood.

35:35.534 --> 35:38.235
My mother loved him.

35:38.237 --> 35:41.671
And he turned his back on her.

35:41.673 --> 35:44.674
Murdering her
and slandering her.

35:44.676 --> 35:46.143
Disowning

35:46.145 --> 35:47.811
and disavowing me,

35:47.813 --> 35:50.714
so that others could
forever do the same.

35:50.716 --> 35:51.781
So that they could

35:51.783 --> 35:53.383
turn to Mary,

35:53.385 --> 35:55.418
the next surviving
legitimate heir.

35:55.420 --> 35:58.371
Elizabeth.

35:58.372 --> 36:01.323
I feared that Mary's wedding
would empower other nations.

36:01.326 --> 36:03.460
But the threat
is from my own people.

36:04.663 --> 36:07.831
I have never felt more forsaken.

36:07.833 --> 36:10.233
It is a portion of your empire.

36:10.235 --> 36:11.268
A key portion!

36:11.270 --> 36:12.569
She could invade!

36:12.571 --> 36:15.772
<i> If</i> she does, she will
not find you alone.

36:15.774 --> 36:18.775
I am here, Elizabeth,
at your side.

36:18.777 --> 36:20.810
And I will not
forsake you.

36:21.947 --> 36:25.482
♪ ♪

36:38.764 --> 36:40.697
MARTIN:
<i> So it went well, then.</i>

36:40.699 --> 36:42.465
The wedding
is a triumph for Mary.

36:42.467 --> 36:44.201
Wasn't your lady friend
upset she brought you

36:44.203 --> 36:46.203
all this way
and she had to attend alone?

36:46.205 --> 36:48.271
I'll attend her in other ways.

36:48.273 --> 36:49.806
How did it go with James?

36:49.808 --> 36:51.608
It didn't go. There is no going.

36:52.844 --> 36:55.212
And if it were
to advance in any way,

36:55.214 --> 36:57.948
that is not information I would
share with you. You are...

36:57.950 --> 36:59.449
(gasps)

36:59.451 --> 37:01.218
Martin,

37:01.220 --> 37:02.819
is Rose wearing earrings?

37:02.821 --> 37:05.222
Did you pierce
my daughter's ears?

37:05.224 --> 37:06.489
<i> Our</i> daughter.

37:06.491 --> 37:08.225
And isn't she gorgeous?

37:08.227 --> 37:10.227
I used ice.
I did it quick as lightning.

37:10.229 --> 37:11.928
She cried for a moment,

37:11.930 --> 37:14.397
but then I held up a looking
glass, and she liked it.

37:14.399 --> 37:17.867
Liked it? She looks like a...
like a fortune teller,

37:17.869 --> 37:19.402
or a...

37:19.404 --> 37:22.005
(sighs) Noble girls
do not have pierced ears.

37:22.007 --> 37:23.640
Pirate babies do.

37:23.642 --> 37:26.943
And she is half pirate.

37:26.945 --> 37:30.013
I left some rubies and emeralds,
a few diamonds.

37:30.015 --> 37:33.617
They'll need to be cut down
to size, settings forged.

37:35.320 --> 37:37.320
That's a small fortune.

37:43.629 --> 37:44.628
(door closes)

37:44.630 --> 37:46.930
James was right.

37:46.932 --> 37:50.834
Life will be richer
in some very unexpected ways.

37:53.639 --> 37:55.805
CATHERINE:
I can help the queen

37:55.807 --> 37:58.742
with whatever she needs to ready
her for her wedding night.

38:00.479 --> 38:01.845
What is it?

38:01.847 --> 38:03.613
(door closes)

38:03.615 --> 38:06.583
The border towns
have been swayed.

38:06.585 --> 38:07.784
How?

38:07.786 --> 38:09.919
Without the Vatican's support?

38:09.921 --> 38:11.855
The gold and silver
jewels and trinkets,

38:11.857 --> 38:13.690
all the wedding
gifts you received.

38:13.692 --> 38:15.925
At first, I thought
I would need to use them

38:15.927 --> 38:17.761
to placate the nobles,

38:17.762 --> 38:19.596
in the event that the
wedding didn't happen.

38:19.598 --> 38:22.499
But once it did,

38:22.501 --> 38:26.336
I had them melted down
and delivered en masse.

38:26.338 --> 38:28.371
To the border.

38:28.373 --> 38:30.874
A gift from their queen.

38:30.876 --> 38:34.377
Catherine, you are brilliant.

38:34.379 --> 38:36.680
Not as brilliant as you,

38:36.682 --> 38:39.349
as your wedding
to Darnley--

38:39.351 --> 38:41.618
an unworthy husband,

38:41.620 --> 38:44.888
to be sure, but the
right man to wed.

38:44.890 --> 38:47.857
Nearly a dozen more
English towns

38:47.859 --> 38:49.359
have turned.

38:49.361 --> 38:51.928
Turned? To Scotland?

38:51.930 --> 38:54.964
They have declared themselves
part of your kingdom.

38:54.966 --> 38:57.967
You have drawn the might
of Catholic nations

38:57.969 --> 38:59.636
to your side,
even as you have

38:59.638 --> 39:01.705
sown tolerance.

39:01.707 --> 39:03.406
And in taking a king,

39:03.408 --> 39:06.409
you have given the people
the promise of an heir,

39:06.411 --> 39:08.611
stability,
something even

39:08.613 --> 39:10.780
Elizabeth's
staunchest supporters

39:10.782 --> 39:12.949
now no longer believe
she will provide.

39:12.951 --> 39:14.984
Still, I can't believe it.

39:14.986 --> 39:18.555
More than a dozen towns
turned so fast.

39:18.557 --> 39:21.091
People love you, Mary.

39:21.093 --> 39:23.026
You have earned
their love

39:23.028 --> 39:25.028
from the moment you
have returned home.

39:25.030 --> 39:27.364
And now we must say good-bye.

39:27.366 --> 39:29.933
The people have gathered

39:29.935 --> 39:32.369
along the corridor
to your chambers.

39:32.371 --> 39:35.372
Darnley went
there directly.

39:35.374 --> 39:37.807
I heard.

39:37.809 --> 39:39.726
Because I am queen,

39:39.727 --> 39:41.644
I could dismiss
the viewing of the consummation.

39:41.646 --> 39:42.979
And there won't be one.

39:42.981 --> 39:44.948
You and I both know
there's no need.

39:44.950 --> 39:49.085
God willing, I will never
have to lay with that man again.

39:49.087 --> 39:51.154
Understood.

39:51.156 --> 39:54.758
Make an excuse tonight
and feign illness tomorrow

39:54.760 --> 39:57.060
and then embark on
trips away from court.

39:57.062 --> 39:59.413
And when you return,

39:59.414 --> 40:01.765
tell him you're pregnant,
making sex out of the question.

40:04.569 --> 40:08.505
But, Mary, you cannot
live the life of a nun.

40:08.507 --> 40:11.574
As you said,
I will have love in my life.

40:11.576 --> 40:14.043
Being a mother, a queen--

40:14.045 --> 40:15.545
it will be
more than enough.

40:15.547 --> 40:16.880
It isn't.

40:16.882 --> 40:18.181
Take it from me.

40:18.183 --> 40:20.049
And even in my youth,

40:20.051 --> 40:21.885
my heart didn't beat
as strongly as yours.

40:21.887 --> 40:24.721
It will drive you
to seek the love of another,

40:24.723 --> 40:27.123
beyond the affection
you bear your child.

40:27.125 --> 40:29.826
Be careful.

40:43.041 --> 40:46.543
(snoring)

40:46.545 --> 40:48.645
The Vatican's man.

40:48.647 --> 40:50.847
Wouldn't the Pope be proud.

40:55.554 --> 40:57.620
(dog barking in distance)

41:05.730 --> 41:07.897
Bothwell.

41:07.899 --> 41:09.499
Please, no.

